# {{ASSISTANT_NAME}} System Map

A short tour of the repo. Every line points at one directory or file.

## Top-level docs

- `README.md`: project overview, tool list, setup, and run commands.
- `SYSTEM-MAP.md`: this file.
- `ASSISTANT-PROFILE.md`: who {{ASSISTANT_NAME}} serves and what kind of assistant it is.
- `OPERATING-CONTRACT.md`: the binding assistant behavior contract for {{ASSISTANT_NAME}}, Claude Code, and Codex sessions.
- `AGENTS.md`: repository guidelines (structure, build/test commands, style, security).
- `CLAUDE.md`: host-level guidance you can paste into your assistant's project or global config.
- `pyproject.toml`: project metadata, dependencies, and the `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}-mcp` console script.
- `.gitignore`: keeps secrets, local state, and work products out of git.
- `.env.example`: documented placeholders for provider credentials and config.

## MCP server

- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/__init__.py`: package marker.
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/mcp/__init__.py`: package marker for the MCP subpackage.
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/mcp/server.py`: the MCP server. Defines `health_check` and the notes tools as thin wrappers over providers; email, calendar, and chat tools are scaffolded as gated stubs.

## Provider integrations

- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/integrations/__init__.py`: package marker.
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/integrations/common.py`: shared helpers (env loading, local paths).
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/integrations/providers/__init__.py`: package marker.
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/integrations/providers/base.py`: provider-agnostic Protocols and ABCs for the capability categories, with interface sketches for email, calendar, and chat providers.
- `{{ASSISTANT_SLUG}}/integrations/providers/notes.py`: the runnable example provider, backed by a local JSON file under `var/`.

## Setup docs

- `docs/integrations/SETUP.md`: how to wire real providers and register the MCP server.

## Playbooks

- `docs/playbooks/README.md`: opt-in domain playbook loading rules.

## Tests

- `tests/test_server_tools.py`: coverage for the MCP tool wrappers using fakes.
- `tests/test_providers.py`: coverage for the notes provider contract and path safety.

## Local-only (gitignored)

- `secrets/`: service-account keys and local tokens.
- `var/`: runtime state, the notes JSON store, and logs.
- `work/`: session work products with a temporary lifecycle.
